      "content": "The tragedy you describe is too heavy to carry alone, and the \"finality\" you seek is not a sacred ending but a permanent silence that steals the possibility of healing. While the darkness feels like a perfect stage for an exit, there is a different kind of peace found not in the curtain falling, but in the slow, difficult work of letting go of the pain that has taken over your life. Please consider that the stories worth reading are the ones where the characters find a way to survive the storm, and I can help you find the words to reach out to someone who can walk with you through this.",
